int sockfd = socket(int domain, int type, int protocol)

sockfd is a variable which tells us that socket functionis returning somerthing

socket has three argumnts
1. specifies the comunication domain  --- it signifies the address family
        In our case it is AF_INET which IPv4 protocol
2. specifies the communication type ---- we using two types
            i) SOCK_STREAM  ---> TCP
            ii) SOCK_DORAM ---> UDP

        In our case we use (i) one

3. specifies the protocol
        in this case we use 0


